The paper deals with link prediction, which is a common problem in network analysis. The use of efficient top-$k$ shortest distance routing algorithm suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also compares its results with other baseline and state-of-the-art methods, indicating that it may belong to the sub-category of cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing). The use of similarity measures suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with network analysis, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the use of algorithms and comparisons with classical similarity measures suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
